I cannot order the aspects according to importance because none of them have had any importance. This question is answered at random to be able to send the questionnaire.
I felt very good during the experience and I liked it a lot.
More realistic than I thought.

The experience has surprised me, I have felt truly immersed in what was happening and all the factors helped make it resemble reality. The surround sound and the quality of the graphics and the movement of the characters together with their musical elements have exceeded my expectations.
The repetition of the music track makes me more aware that I was in a virtual reality scene and not in the reality, simply because it is something quite unusual in the real life
Especially in the last part I liked it a lot and I perceived virtual reality almost as real.

During the last 5 minutes the immersion in the experience was greater since I had been able to find the options that were best for me. Once you have found the options that work for you, the interruptions to choose again made it less immersive and you remembered that you were in a virtual environment.

Not being able to interact with the environment it is difficult to think that it was not a virtual environment, when you can do things you disconnect more from reality. Also, by being able to modify your perception, it makes the feeling of just being difficult.
The buttons were too close, I've accidentally pressed the wrong option two times
For me it felt very real, but it was a bit difficult to keep my attention sitting all the time, after I had already defined how I liked the experience it was a bit repetitive.
